==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Oxyacid
<hw>Ox`y*ac"id</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[<ets>Oxy-</ets>
<sd>(a)</sd> + <ets>acid</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>An acid
containing oxygen, as chloric acid or sulphuric acid; -- contrasted with
the <contr>hydracids</contr>, which contain no oxygen, as hydrochloric
acid. See <er>Acid</er>, and <er>Hydroxy-</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Oxyammonia</ent>⟦br⟧
